commText: Atharva Taide and Bairstow are at the crease. Atharva Taide is on strike. Boult will open the attack
Boult to Atharva Taide, wide, gentle start from Boult, pushed one full and down leg, past Taide's flick and it's called as a wide
Boult to Atharva Taide, no run, on a good length and around the off-stump channel, flicked crisply and straight to the fielder at mid-wicket
Boult to Atharva Taide, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, Taide leans forward and pushes it into the gap wide of mid-off, he's off the mark with a single
Boult to Bairstow, no run, on a good length and just outside off - a half-stride forward as Bairstow defended it to the off-side
Boult to Bairstow, 1 run, fraction fuller and just outside off, dropped in front of cover and Bairstow is off for a quick single
Boult to Atharva Taide, no run, back of a length and shaping away from wide of off, Taide pokes half-heartedly and is beaten on the outside edge
Boult to Atharva Taide, 1 run, short of a length and angling into the body, drops to the off-side and Taide is off for a quick single
Kuldeep Sen, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Kuldeep Sen to Atharva Taide, FOUR, creamed, overpitched and wide of off - Taide leans across, plays with an open face and then finds the gap square past cover-point, races away to the ropes

Kuldeep Sen to Atharva Taide, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Taide - pitched up by Kuldeep, but the length is too full and wide of off, lets Taide lean into the drive and place it to the left of cover, runs away to the ropes

Kuldeep Sen to Atharva Taide, 2 runs, Kuldeep drags the length back, but the line is a tad too straight, clipped off the back-foot past mid-wicket, the fielder chase and then fumbles, allowing a second
Kuldeep Sen to Atharva Taide, 1 run, another fumble, has ben a shaky start from RR - fuller length delivery outside off and was driven to cover, he doesn't stop it cleanly and allows a single
Kuldeep Sen to Bairstow, 1 run, short and wide of off, Bairstow cuts it to deep backward point for a single
Kuldeep Sen to Atharva Taide, 1 run, short of a good length and well wide of off, Taide throws his hands on the drive and gets a single to deep point, 13 off the over
Boult to Atharva Taide, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, Taide prods forward and pushes it to cover
Boult to Atharva Taide, 1 run, Boult shortens the length on off, nudged in front of mid-on for a quick single
Boult to Bairstow, no run, on a good length and pushed across the right-hander, Bairstow steers with an open face and can't beat short third
Boult to Bairstow, FOUR, beautifully played, overpitched by Boult, Bairstow leans forward, presents a straight bat and then drives it back past the non-striker, races away to the straight boundary
Boult to Bairstow, 1 run, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, nudged in front of mid-wicket for a quick single
Boult to Atharva Taide, 2 wides, banged in short and at the left-hander, went sailing over Taide's head and Samson does well to leap and plam it over, saved at least three more runs for his team
Boult to Bairstow, 1 run, full and wide of off, Bairstow reaches across and toe-ends the drive to the left of cover for a single
Avesh Khan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Avesh Khan to Bairstow, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Bairstow presses forward and pushes it back at the bowler
Avesh Khan to Bairstow, no run, short and skidding through at pace, Bairstow was shaping for the pull, doesn't bounce as much as he expected and raps him high on the thigh-pad
Avesh Khan to Bairstow, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off - Bairstow plays away from his body and skews an inside edge past the leg-stump
Avesh Khan to Atharva Taide, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Avesh Khan to Atharva Taide, out Caught by Kuldeep Sen!! A massive top-edge on the pull, goes straight up and Samson calls for the catch, so does Kuldeep at short third man, a minor collision, but Kuldeep held on and has a word with his captain, was always his catch and he makes Samson know. Banged in short and following Taide as he came down the pitch, he tries to pull, gets cramped for room and only manages a top-edge - Kuldeep didn't have to move an inch as he accepted it with glee. Atharva Taide c Kuldeep Sen b Avesh Khan 15(12) [4s-2]
Prabhsimran Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, on a length and just outside off, defended with an open face to the off-side
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven to the left of mid-off for a single
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, full and a hint of swing back into the right-hander, driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, on a good length and just outside off - a half-forward stride as Prabhsimran defended
Boult to Prabhsimran, 1 run, back of a length and angling across the right-hander, steered to backward point's right where Maharaj dives and makes a good stop, keeping them down to a single
Boult to Bairstow, 1 run, the inswinger from Boult, Bairstow covers for it and then pushes it in front of mid-off for a quick single
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, on a good length and well wide of off, a half-hearted stab as Prabhsimran drove away from hid body, bounces through to mid-off
Boult to Prabhsimran, 1 run, fuller length delivery at the pads, clipped behind square on the on-side for a single

1-5 Over Summary: >> Boult begins the innings with a miserly 4-run over >> Taide strikes back-to-back boundaries off Kuldeep Sen >> Bairstow gains confidence with a boundary in Boult’s 2nd over >> Avesh gets rid of Taide in his 1st over >> PBKS are 31/1 after 5 overs
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, pushed to the right of point for a single
Avesh Khan to Bairstow, 1 run, back of a length and well wide of off, chopped behind square on the off-side for a single
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, banged in short by Avesh as Singh came running down the pitch, he swings and misses, called as one for the over
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, fuller length delivery on off, Prabhsimran went too hard on the drive, the bottom-hand takes control and he drags it to mid-on
Trent Boult in the Powerplay in IPL 2024 \nFirst three matches: 5/58 (9 overs, SR: 10.8, ER: 6.44) \nNext three matches: 0/39 (7 overs, ER: 5.57)
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, FOUR, drilled, much needed for the Kings, overpitched and wide of off - Prabhsimran leans into the drive and drills it over mid-off, one bounce and over the ropes
Avesh Khan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, on a good length and angling into the pads, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single - end of a pretty unproductive batting PP for the Kings
Time for Chahal..
Yuzvendra Chahal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chahal to Prabhsimran, wide, tossed up and sliding down leg, called as a wide
Chahal to Prabhsimran, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle, Prabhsimran goes back and works it through mid-wicket for a single
Chahal to Bairstow, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, nudged in front of mid-wicket for a single
Chahal to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chahal to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! That's ugly and Prabhsimran has holed out to wide long-on - came down the pitch, got too close to the ball, no timing on the lofted drive, hits it into the wind and the ball sails down the throat of Jurel, who doesn't drop those. A first-over wicket for Chahal and Punjab continue to struggle. Prabhsimran c Dhruv Jurel b Chahal 10(14) [4s-1]
Sam Curran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chahal to Sam Curran, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, pushed down to long-off for a single
Chahal to Bairstow, no run, loopy delivery on the leg-stump line, Bairstow was shaping for the flick and missed, rolled to the on-side and he wanted a single, sent back by his partner
Chahal to Bairstow, no run, flighted delivery on off, defended back at the bowler

Lowest Powerplay scores in IPL 2024 27/3 - PBKS vs SRH, Mullanpur 31/2 - RR vs DC, Jaipur 32/2 - CSK vs DC, Visakhapatnam 38/1 - PBKS vs RR, Mullanpur 40/1 - PBKS vs RCB, Bengaluru PBKS’s powerplay run-rate of 7.77 is the second-lowest this season after RR’s 7.6.
Spin from both ends and it's Keshav Maharaj
Keshav Maharaj, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Maharaj to Sam Curran, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Curran backs away and cuts it to deep point for a single
Maharaj to Bairstow, no run, tossed up on off, Bairstow pushes forward and finds cover with the block
Maharaj to Bairstow, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, Bairstow backs away and chops it to cover where Hetmyer fumbles and allows a single
Maharaj to Sam Curran, 1 run, pushed through by Maharaj, Curran rocks back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket
Maharaj to Bairstow, 2 runs, nicely played, tossed up at the stumps - Curran backs away and then cuts it off the stumps, places it square past point and he's back for the second
Maharaj to Bairstow, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Maharaj to Bairstow, out Caught by Hetmyer!! That's the end of a laborious knock and it's also Maharaj's first IPL wicket. He tossed up one slower and just outside off, a hint of spin and Bairstow had to reach out on the drive after having backed away initially, hit high on the bat and spooned for a dolly to Hetmyer at cover. He never got going tonight and has had a painful stay ended. Bairstow c Hetmyer b Maharaj 15(19) [4s-1]
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Sen [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Sen to Sam Curran, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, hit high on the bat as Curran looked to cut, bounces back at the bowler
Kuldeep Sen to Sam Curran, no run, on a good length and at the stumps, Curran leans across and tucks it to mid-wicket
Kuldeep Sen to Sam Curran, no run, fraction fuller and on off, pushed back at the bowler
Kuldeep Sen to Sam Curran, 1 run, length ball at the pads, clipped behind square on the on-side for a single
Bairstow vs LA orthodox in the IPL Runs: 120 Balls: 114 Dismissals: 6 Avg: 20 SR: 105.3 Dots: 56
Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, short and at the body, pulled past square leg for a single
Bairstow vs Maharaj in T20s Runs: 29 Balls: 29 Dismissals: 2 Avg: 14.5 SR: 100 Dots: 12
Kuldeep Sen to Sam Curran, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, Curran inner halves the push to mid-on for a single, brings up the 50 for the Kings

Time for the strategic break. This doesn't look like a great batting track - it's on the slower side and has been exploited well by the bowlers. Three batters got starts and none reached even 20. Anything around 150 could be a fighting score if there's now dew later on
Maharaj to Sam Curran, 1 run, pushed through by Maharaj, pulled down to long-on for a single
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, punched down to long-on for a single
Maharaj to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Maharaj to Sam Curran, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! Catching practice at deep mid-wicket, nothing is going right for the Punjab Kings at the moment. Dropped short by Maharaj and the pull was on - Curran rocked back on the shot, but he's hit it off the lower half of the bat, dragged the pull towards deep mid-wicket where Jurel ran in, slid forward and took a fine catch. Sam Curran c Dhruv Jurel b Maharaj 6(10)
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Maharaj to Shashank Singh, 1 run, Shashank's in good touch and he shows some intent straightaway - comes down the pitch, doesn't get close to the ball, went through with the lofted drive and chips it back over the bowler's head
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, no run, flighted delivery on off, pushed back at the bowler

Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, no run, a pleading appeal for LBW, Maharaj kept asking and asking, the umpire says NO and they review. Jitesh was shaping for the big sweep, did he get an edge on that? No, it's a flat line on UltraEdge. Onto ball-tracking: it's umpire's call on impact and that's what saves Jitesh, it's smashing into the middle-stump otherwise. A decent stride as Jitesh went for the sweep and he missed, struck on the pad and marginally in front of off-stump

6-10 Over Summary: >> Prabhsimran hammers one over mid-off for a boundary >> Prabhsimran holes out to long-on in Chahal’s 1st over >> Maharaj gets his 1st IPL wicket by dismissing Bairstow >> Maharaj strikes again as he gets rid of Sam Curran >> A tight LBW call goes in favour of Jitesh
Yuzvendra Chahal [1.0-0-4-1] is back into the attack
Chahal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single

Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, wide, the wrong 'un, Jitesh Sharma looks to flick and missed. It's not given as a wide and PBKS review. Did it flick the pad on its way to the keeper? Onto UltraEdge and it's a flat line, so it's a wide and it's a successful review
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, dropped short and on off, punched square on the off-side for a single
Chahal to Shashank Singh, no run, very full and sliding onto the pads, Shashank was shaping for the flick and missed

Chahal to Shashank Singh, no run, the big leg-break now, bowled slower through the air, dragged Shashank into the drive and spun past the outside edge - Samson was quick to break the stumps, but Shashank hadn't gone anywhere
Chahal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, punched down to long-on for a single
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, pushed through by Chahal, eased down to long-on for a single
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, hammered, tossed up on middle and leg - Jitesh backs away, comes down the pitch and then hammers the drive over the bowler's head, one bounce and over the ropes
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, dragged short by Maharaj - Jitesh makes room and cuts it to deep cover for a single
Maharaj to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, driven down to long-off for a single
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, the arm-ball now, Jitesh makes room and cuts it square past point for a single
Maharaj to Shashank Singh, FOUR, nicely played, slower and wider of off, Shashank reaches out and then drives it over cover, bounces away to the ropes
Maharaj to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, nudged through mid-wicket for a single, 12 off the over
Kuldeep Sen [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Sen to Shashank Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Sen to Shashank Singh, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! They're finding the fielders everywhere tonight - back of a length and angling into the right-hander, Shashank picked the length and then swivelled across on the pull, he got a lot of height and no real distance, high and down Jurel's throat, who completes his 3rd catch of the night, running to his left from deep square leg. Shashank Singh c Dhruv Jurel b Kuldeep Sen 9(9) [4s-1]
Liam Livingstone, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Kuldeep Sen to Livingstone, 1 run, edged and dropped - back of a length and well wide of off, Livingstone was flat-footed as he played with an open face, gets a thick edge to the keeper's right - Samson dives and gets a hand onto it, but he can't hold on and the chance goes in waste
Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, no run, on a good length and around the off-stump channel, defended to the off-side
Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, pushed off the back-foot to the off-side
Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, no run, on a length and at the pads, tucked straight to the fielder at mid-wicket
Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, fuller length delivery on off, nudged in front of square on the on-side for a single
Time for the strategic break. It's been a tough night for the Kings and the batting has floundered. It hasn't been straightforward, but they haven't batted well either. Can they get to 140+?
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, coming in with the arm and on a length, Jitesh Sharma tucks it through mid-wicket
Maharaj to Livingstone, no run, full ball drifting into middle, Livingstone bunts it back to Maharaj
Maharaj to Livingstone, 1 run, on the shorter side outside off, Livingstone rocks back and cuts it to the left of deep point for a run

Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, no run, quicker and flatter, coming in towards the leg-stump, Jitesh Sharma looks to sweep it hard but is struck on the thigh pad. Livingstone looks for a run but it's not on

Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, no run, close shave! Jitesh Sharma makes room and looks to open up the off-side but he is deceived in the flight. Gets beaten on the swing as the ball goes past the leg-stump
Maharaj to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, Jitesh Sharma uses his feet and knocks this one down to long-off. Maharaj bowls out with figures of: 4-0-23-2. Brilliant stuff from him
Yuzvendra Chahal [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, on a back of a length on off, goes straight on, Jitesh Sharma cuts it to sweeper cover
Chahal to Livingstone, 1 run, tossed up generously and drifting in, stroked down to long-on
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, slow through the air once again, Jitesh Sharma drives it hard as it goes past the non-striker towards long-on
Chahal to Livingstone, 1 run, the googly on a back of a length on off, Livingstone reads it off the pitch and punches it to long-on

Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, gorgeous! Jitesh Sharma sees this one wide outside off and floated up and his eyes lit up. He makes room, advances, and plays a wonderful lofted stroke over deep extra cover for a 83m six
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, the wrong 'un on a fuller length, Jitesh Sharma might have picked it as he drags his sweep to deep square leg
Kuldeep Sen [3.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack

11-15 Over Summary >> Jitesh breaks the shackles by hitting a boundary after 31 balls >> Maharaj concedes 12 in his 3rd over >> Kuldeep Sen comes back into the attack and bounces out Shashank Singh >> Livingstone is dropped first ball by Samson off Kuldeep’s bowling>> >> Maharaj ends a fine spell, his figures: 4-0-23-2.

Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, brilliant shot! Long-off is up inside the ring and Jitesh Sharma takes full advantage. It's in the slot alright but the bat swing from Jitesh Sharma is spot on. He crunches it down the ground for a biggie
Kuldeep Sen to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, back of a length ball outside off, Jitesh Sharma tries to punch it through covers but ekes an inside edge towards mid-wicket
Kuldeep Sen to Livingstone, no run, pacy back of a length ball well outside off, Livingstone doesn't go after it

Kuldeep Sen to Livingstone, no run, good length ball shaping in sharply, a wild swing from Livingstone as he is struck on the thigh pad. He doesn't quite know where the ball is as he advances out of his crease. The bowler charges in and he then rushes back

Kuldeep Sen to Livingstone, FOUR, fuller length ball angling in on off, Livingstone heaves it over mid-wicket and beats the fielder in the deep to his left. Not off the meat of the bat but Livingstone is a powerful man
Deep mid-wicket in place now. Third man comes inside the ring

Kuldeep Sen to Livingstone, SIX, 100 up for PBKS! A slot delivery for Livingstone around off. He doesn't miss out on those as he swipes it handsomely over deep square leg for a big maximum. He is starting to take off. 17 runs off the over, the biggest of the innings so far
Avesh is stopped by Jitesh Sharma in his delivery stride. He was not quite ready and Avesh has a banter with him
Avesh Khan [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Avesh Khan to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Avesh Khan to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Riyan Parag!! Avesh gets his second wicket! A skiddy good length ball angling in on off, Jitesh Sharma tries to go over mid-off but he completely miscues it. Parag inside the ring takes an easy catch. Jitesh Sharma looked promising tonight but fell before his innings could blossom. Jitesh Sharma c Riyan Parag b Avesh Khan 29(24) [4s-1 6s-2]
Ashutosh Sharma comes in as the Impact player for Prabhsimran Singh for PBKS
Ashutosh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, full length ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma drives it down to mid-on to get off the mark
Avesh Khan to Livingstone, 1 run, slower back of a length ball outside off, Livingstone taps it towards backward point and calls his partner through for a brisk single
Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, leg byes, 1 run, good length ball shaping towards the leg-stump, Ashutosh Sharma looks to swipe but it deflects off his pads towards mid-wicket for a leg bye

Avesh Khan to Livingstone, FOUR, well played! A very full ball moving in on off, almost a yorker length ball. Livingstone clears his front leg and hits it through wide mid-on. Deep mid-wicket moves to his left but he has no chance
Avesh Khan to Livingstone, 1 run, fullish ball angling in, perhaps a slot ball but Livingstone looks to hit it too hard and mistimes it to deep backward square leg
Yuzvendra Chahal [3.0-0-20-1] is back into the attack

Chahal to Livingstone, 1 run, slow through the air and on a back of a length outside off, sticks on the surface, Livingstone looks to chop it through the off-side but gets an inside edge past Samson for a single
Chahal to Ashutosh Sharma, no ball, the attempted googly but it drifts down leg, goes past Ashutosh Sharma's big swing. Chahal has overstepped and a Free Hit is coming up...
Chahal to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, tosses this one generously wide outside off, away from Ashutosh Sharma's hitting arc and he can only drag his shot towards backward square leg
Chahal to Livingstone, leg byes, 1 run, the googly that drifts in as Livingstone makes room. Deflects off his pads and rolls towards point for a leg bye
Chahal to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, smashed! On a back of a length outside off, slow through the air and Ashutosh Sharma has ample time to line it up. He tonks it over wide long-on for a maximum
Chahal to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Chahal to Ashutosh Sharma, out Livingstone Run Out!! 1 run completed! Tossed up full ball on middle and leg, Ashutosh Sharma drags his heave towards deep mid-wicket. Livingstone wants the second but he has been sent back. He is struggling to get back as Samson collects the flat throw to his left and gets low to throw it back onto the stumps. It is taken upstairs and Livingstone is short. Brilliant tag-team work from Kotian and Samson. Livingstone run out (Tanush Kotian/Samson) 21(14) [4s-2 6s-1]
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chahal to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, a low full-toss on off, Harpreet Brar drives it to sweeper cover to retain strike
Avesh Khan to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, a skiddy good length ball on middle and leg, Harpreet Brar blocks it towards mid-wicket to get off strike

Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, dropped! Confusion between the bowler and the keeper and it goes down. A fullish ball angling in. Ashutosh Sharma tries to heave it and miscues it towards mid-wicket. Avesh Khan is running towards it and is closer to the ball but Samson charges in. Both go for it but neither can hang on.
Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, shot! In the arc for Ashutosh Sharma. He lines it up and smashes it over wide long-on for another maximum

Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, a pinpoint yorker on off, Ashutosh Sharma carves it towards short third and takes off. A needless throw from the fielder at the striker's end and the batters take another run off the overthrow

Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, Ashutosh Sharma has got some hitting talent! On a back of a length around off, Ashutosh Sharma makes room and flat-bats it towards long-off. Parag leaps but he can only see it sailing over the fence
Avesh Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, a very full ball wide outside off, Ashutosh Sharma reaches out to it and guides it to third man to retain strike
Trent Boult [3.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, a slower short ball angling down from round the wicket, Ashutosh Sharma looks to pull it across but misses. Not wided by the umpire as it sailed over his gloves
Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, FOUR, hammered! A full ball outside off, Ashutosh Sharma with a firm base smashes it past extra cover for a rocketing boundary. Hit that one so hard

Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, a low full-toss wide outside off, near the tramline, Ashutosh Sharma lets it go. Called as wide on-field. The replay shows that it was just within the tramline and the review works for RR
Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, a slower fuller length ball, Ashutosh Sharma swipes it towards deep square leg
Boult to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, Harpreet Brar premeditates as he shuffles across his stumps. The low full-toss tails in towards off as Harpreet Brar scoops it towards backward square leg
Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Maharaj!! Ashutosh Sharma falls after playing a gem of a cameo! A short ball that rushes Ashutosh Sharma for pace. He looks to pull it across but top-edges it towards backward point. Maharaj makes no mistake. Ashutosh Sharma c Maharaj b Boult 31(16) [4s-1 6s-3]

21:13 Local Time, 15:43 GMT, 21:13 IST: A good recovery in the backend from PBKS but the damage was done before that. RR chose to bowl first and their bowlers repaid the faith the captain had in them. Taide departed cheaply and Prabhsimran couldn't get going either. Bairstow played an uncharacteristic knock as he looked sluggish and struggled for rhythm. The Englishman eventually mistimed one against Maharaj and walked off. The RR bowlers kept the pressure on as the spinners took over in the middle overs after the new-ball bowlers. The wicket did hold up and Chahal and Maharaj in particular bowled brilliantly. Wickets kept falling at regular intervals and PBKS couldn't inject any sort of momentum into ther innings in that phase. Jitesh started to play a few expansive shots but couldn't convert his start. Livingstone played a cameo to build some momentum but the real impact came from the Impact player, Ashutosh Sharma. He hit the ball cleanly and took his side close to the 150-run mark. This surface is nowhere near to the surfaces that were used in the last two games here. RR will still fancy themselves but a few wickets upfront can certainly make things interesting. Join us shortly for the run-chase...
PBKS innings progression Overs 1-3: 26/0 (RR: 8.67) Overs 4-14: 49/5 (RR: 4.45) Overs 15-19: 66/2 (RR: 13.2) Last over: 6/1
- This is the third-lowest first-innings score in IPL 2024, after MI’s 125/9 against RR at Wankhede and KKR’s 137/9 vs CSK at Chepauk.

Most runs in Overs 18-20 in IPL 2024 91(35) - Dinesh Karthik (SR: 260) 86(31) - Heinrich Klaasen (SR: 277.42) 85(36) - Ashutosh Sharma (SR: 236.11) 75(39) - Nicholas Pooran (SR: 192.31) 73(41) - Rahul Tewaita (SR: 178.05)
- Dhruv Jurel became the first fielder to bag three catches in an IPL innings on two different occasions for RR, having previously done so against LSG in Jaipur earlier this season.

Keshav Maharaj - He's been phenomenal (On Yuzvendra Chahal), has been a world class performer, both at the domestic level and at the international level, and I am mighty proud to have played with him. It started to get better towards the latter half, it was a bit stoppy at the start (on the conditions), hopefully we'll chase this score down.
